    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>HAVERSTRAW: FERRY SERVICE TO BEGIN</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ELSA BRENNER</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Metropolitan Transportation Authority approves demonstration project to provide rush-hour ferry service between Haverstraw and Ossining, NY, in order to relieve congestion on Tappan Zee Bridge (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Metropolitan Transportation Authority has approved a demonstration project to provide rush-hour ferry service between Haverstraw and Ossining beginning next month. The goal is to relieve congestion on the Tappan Zee Bridge. Commuters can park in Haverstraw in Rockland County and take a NY Waterway ferry to Ossining. Service is to begin at 6:30 a.m. to meet a Metro-North express from Ossining due at Grand Central before 7:30 a.m. The combined ferry-train monthly commuting pass will be $198. A single ferry ticket will be $3.</p>
        <p>ELSA BRENNER</p>
      </block>
